description: The incredibly popular online animated series makes its jump into comic books! Dirge is an undead man with a mind of his own, who struggles to find the meaning of unlife - all the while fighting to protect human lives from evil zombies! Don't miss this epic quest to save humanity!

Zoe just can't obey and just can't stay out of trouble... Once she's reunited with Dirge, everything hits the fan! When a zombie with unchartered abilities attacks living humans, can the survivors bring themselves to trust Dirge to protect them? Can human and zombie work together? They're going to have to if they want to survive the dark days that are coming!

The last survivors of humanity have one line of defense left between them and the zombie hordes that would destroy all -- a bastion that is quickly fading away... Their only hope is Dirge, a zombie that is determined to see humanity protected! Can he survive the attacks he faces in order to help humanity in time?!

The desperate race against the clock continues! Dirge and Zoe are on a time-sensitive mission to save the last remnants of humanity, but are being massively slowed down by brutal attacks from every side! Though it all, the dangerous and mysterious Gallows makes his move against Dirge...

Dirge's worst nightmare comes true... Is Zoe truly a zombie now? Can Dirge destroy one of the only people he cares for?! Can he even hope to defeat Gallows in personal combat? Plus, the machines shut down... The last of humanity is completely vulnerable... the zombie hordes are swarming...

Three complete stories - 'The Necromancer,' 'The Company Man,' and 'Gravedigger's Banquet' - all from the 1970's including Dave Sim's abortive attempts to break in at Charlton Comics, complete with rejection letters from Charlton editor George Wildman.
name: Cerebus in Chains; The Company Man; Gravedigger's Banquet

description: If ANYONE ever told you that a ferret had helped win the war you'd think he was crazy. Yet if it hadn't been for Sid Bundy's pet ferret, Flight-Lieutenant Jack Linton wouldn't have ended up taking a bomber crew on their first mission - a flight that was to have the most suprising results...
name: BUNDY'S SECRET WEAPON

description: Los Angeles, 1953: Home to bent cops, smooth criminals, and curvaceous starlets; where the glamour and wealth of Hollywood and Beverly Hills collide with the crime and grit of Chinatown. Amidst this startling contrast, American ideals are under siege by Joseph McCarthy and the H.U.A.C. trials, rooting out communist threats where ever they may lie - even in the ranks of the super heroic! Can there be any doubt about the loyalties of L.A.'s greatest and most patriotic hero, the Eagle? America is about to find out the hard way!
name: Unmasked

description: Shunned by the public that once adored him, and even questioned by his own daughter, The Eagle thinks things can't get worse...until he's arrested as a Soviet spy.
name: The Eagle And The Bear

description: Stripped of his honor and thrown into jail, The Eagle thinks he's hit rock bottom - and then things get even worse! Can his wannabe sidekick, The Falcon, pull him out in time...or will the young hero get pulled down along with his idol?
name: Broken Eagle

description: The Eagle's under house arrest when The Grey Falcon - the young hero who idolizes him - gets nabbed by mobsters. Will the Eagle risk a prison sentence on Alcatraz to rescue his protégé?
name: Nighthawks

description: Imprisoned on Alcatraz, the Eagle discovers an unlikely ally. Meanwhile, the Eagle's protégé, the Grey Falcon, hatches a plan to break his hero out...but will the Eagle's daughter help or hinder?
name: A Hard Place

description: Events come to an earth-shattering conclusion as the Red Menace's plan to nuke Los Angeles with a Soviet A-bomb are set in motion. Can the Eagle save the city that turned on him? And will he?
name: The Eagle And The Falcon

volume.name: Adventures in Reading Starring the Amazing Spider-Man

description: Adapts The First Men on the Moon. Despite the cover proclaiming this was adapted from a Jules Verne's story, that novel was actually written by H.G. Wells; Verne wrote From the Earth to the Moon, an entirely different story.
name: The First Men in the Moon

description:
A Preview to Alan Moore's Neonomicon.  In this issue a few pages from issue #1 was used to show us readers the bridge connection to The Courtyard, assuming we have read it.
 
The rest of the comic was filled with pages from Alan Moore's scripts.

The Coming of.. Witch-Woman

Reprint of Marvel Spotlight #10

The Hangin' of Angus O'Donnel

Starring Phantom Rider
name: The Coming of.. Witch-Woman

description: Agents Sugarman and Gere barely escaped death at the talons of Neuerman Giesel's enhanced bio-weapons, and their unit is down to just a few soldiers. Low on ammo, they've discovered Giesel's secret and stand ready to take the fight to him. The only thing standing in their way is the army of T-Virus infected zombies pouring out of the jungle…

name: Rotting Metal, Rusted Flesh / Playing with Coal
Diagram of the Heart Pumping Blood / Like an Ember Mist at Dusk
Ghosts of Heroes I Once Knew
